MPUMALANGA cops have launched a manhunt for 15 fake cops armed with guns who robbed Pakistani traders in Hazyview on Sunday, 16 January. Police spokesman Brigadier Selvy Mohlala, said: “Fifteen armed men entered the flats at about 7.45pm by damaging the gate before breaking the doors with a crowbar. “Some were allegedly wearing balaclavas and police uniforms, while others were allegedly wearing Hawks’ jackets. “It’s further alleged that during the robbery, one suspect stabbed three victims in their backs and handcuffed them with cable ties,” he said. Mohlala said the suspects then demanded money and ransacked their rooms, where they took cellphones, laptops, other valuable items and an undisclosed amount of cash. Anyone with information which can help with the arrest of the suspects should contact Captain Eurence Sibuyi on 082 449 0231.